child.pub-comments: Total population: ca. 52,000. (Voorhoeve 1975: 369) Voorhoeve writes that many of the languages in this family have extremely high percentages of cognates between languages: "Iria and Asienara share nearly 80% cognates, [and] the other percentages within the family range form 50% to 70%." He also notes that there are no clear subgroups within this family, though, due to the high percentage of cognates between them, the languages Iria and Asienara seem more closely bound than the others of this family. (Voorhoeve 1975: 369)
